message: she for sure had her autonomy stage - we can see how she's been watching daily shows and collecting information about englishmen's behavior and british way of life

Joy really had her honeymoon phase - she calls it tourist phase - during which she's been finding everything completely new and exciting. she probably had her distress stage - where she understood that the stereotypes which she took with here to london were not completely true. but I'm not sure about other stages, especially re-integration. she didn't seem to be angry or disliking london and englishmen. though, we all can agree she is now on her independence stage

in an article I've read what the culture shock is. for this person writing it, it was a quite surprising experience. Joy had her own stereotypes about london and englishmen's behavior, and in this article we see how she faces it every day, deals with it and discovers real society.
Joy really had her honeymoon phase - she calls it tourist phase - during which she's been finding everything completely new and exciting. she probably had her distress stage - where she understood that the stereotypes which she took with here to london were not completely true. but I'm not sure about other stages, especially re-integration. she didn't seem to be angry or disliking london and englishmen. though, we all can agree she is now on her independence stage
 she also gives a piece of advice: don't be afraid to try out new, but check some sources before you go somewhere.

I think the medium today to create the greatest impact are mobile applications which can be used to address a humanitarian need. The great thing about mobile apps are available distribution channels which can effectively help you reach your target audience. Few ideas of good causes:
1. Different readers for the visually impaired
2. A social app which can make distribution of food that is left in events to the ones whom really need it. This is a great read on the topic http://www.feld.com/wp/archives/2013/05/the-incredible-waste-of-food-at-events.html
3. Free learning tools for kids in areas where education is not accessible .

- We are deeply convinced that waterfall fits our project, as it is global. There are a lot of functions we need to implement in our technology. Consequently, we should dedicate resources to small parts, so personnel can work simultaneously while completing their specific tasks.
For example, developing an Artificial Intelligence, an app, a device, developing design and etc.

- We need a great deal of well-qualified workers for our start-up so it will not be possible to make everybody collaborate.

- Because of the huge amount of high technology we have to agree on all requirements at the beginning. 

- Additionally, we need a project manager in our company to be in charge of people as well as their organization.

As our project is a global one,there are a lot of functions we want  to implement in our technology. So we should dedicate resources to small parts. so personnel  can work in parallel doing their specific tasks.

message:
Flo Period Tracker is much more than a "women's menstruation calendar". More than 200 million women around the world already use it!
 
The calendar of the cycle will help track menstruation and PMS, calculate the days of ovulation and conception, learn useful information about the development of pregnancy and monitor the development of the baby. Flo's menstrual calendar is the first app (menstrual diary) that uses artificial intelligence to determine the irregular cycle of menstruation, ovulation, and PMS symptoms.
 
 
Modern technologies based on machine learning make it possible to make the most accurate prediction of the onset of critical days and ovulation.
 
You can enter all the data you need and receive reminders about when your cycle will start.
 
Install a flo women's calendar and enjoy all the advantages of modern developments to feel comfortable at any time.


MY WOMEN'S MENSTRUATION CALENDAR AND OVULATION CALCULATOR
‚Ä¢ follow the cycle, receive reminders about critical days and time of ovulation

‚Ä¢ a monthly diary will help to track the irregularity of the cycle

‚Ä¢ calculate the days of ovulation and determine your "fertility window"

‚Ä¢ use to conceive a child (menstruation and ovulation calculator will help you find out on which days the probability of getting pregnant is maximum)

‚Ä¢ save your test results

‚Ä¢ analyze basal body temperature (BTT)

‚Ä¢ flag symptoms to get the most accurate predictions of your cycle


PREGNANCY (CONCEPTION) CALCULATOR
‚Ä¢ help with calculations of ovulation days

‚Ä¢ plan the day of conception of the child (determination of ovulation)

‚Ä¢ track pregnancy week by week

‚Ä¢ read useful tips and relevant articles about pregnancy, menstruation, women's health

‚Ä¢ keep a personal diary so you don't miss any important date


LIFESTYLE
‚Ä¢ watch your weight, sleep duration, amount of water you drink, basal body temperature

‚Ä¢ mark physical activity

‚Ä¢ monitor your sex life and mood

‚Ä¢ Notice and add PMS symptoms

‚Ä¢ track and mark selections


REMINDERS
‚Ä¢ about the beginning of the cycle and ovulation

‚Ä¢ on taking contraceptives, pills


GRAPHICS
‚Ä¢ save the history of your cycles and analyze their length (to make it easier to calculate the ovulation calendar)

‚Ä¢ BBT and ovulation graphs

‚Ä¢ changes in cycle length

‚Ä¢ change in weight and activity during the day


INDIVIDUALLY AND JUST FOR YOU
‚Ä¢ Flo will help you learn more information about your body

‚Ä¢ read useful articles about health every day

‚Ä¢ get useful advice from professional doctors



WOMEN'S CALENDAR SETTINGS
‚Ä¢ protect your personal data with a password

‚Ä¢ choose your app design



Set up a women's calendar and join the 70 million girls and women who already trust Flo's women's diary.



Discover the most popular female health & well-being guide chosen by 200M women, co-created with 100+ leading health & medical experts, and acclaimed medical institutions.

‚Ä¢ Partner of the United Nations Population Fund in the area of reproductive health
‚Ä¢ 100+ doctors and health experts are part of the Flo Medical Board

message:
Muse (MultiSense)

Our product is focused on different senses that we have in our body: sight, hearing and touch. This is a sophisticated "box" which is capable of a huge amount of features. It has 3 sections, each applies to its own organ sense: yellow is responsible for sight, red - hearing, violet - touch. You can listen to a wide variety of podcasts, songs or interviews with a help of yellow part as well as speaking to the artificial intelligence. The red one can provide you with various practical games, quizes and diagrams, which are personally picked by artificial intelligence due to your interests. Violet element has the highest stage of perfomance: while you study, it changes the box‚Äôs temperature or give you electric impulses when your answers are incorrect. However this function may be switched off. We present the education of future. 

This product is undoubtedly innovative as it has a personal adviser installed inside. Due to its unbelievable features, artificial intelligence adviser provides you with a reasonable analysis of the mistakes and comes up with personal comments, articles for you. The main goal is education through practice and feedback from artificial intelligence. 

Our target audience includes busy people of any age, who are ready to experience the new type of emotions simultaneously being able to learn new information in any sphere. 

Muse is challenging in developing, although it will be amazingly popular among people and, from our point of view, will make a fortune.

message:
So, Flo is an app I use every day to control my cycle and watch symptoms that depend on a part of the cycle. I will quickly show you how it looks and what you can do there and then read the company‚Äôs description.

Track your cycle
With the help of Flo you don‚Äôt need to have a paper calendar and carry it with you to doctors. You can easily find the day of the cycle in the app and check where your last period had started.

Mark your state every day
As both physical and mental health depend on the specific days of the cycle, you can mark how you feel every day to control your state. As you can see, there are lots of sections you can choose to mark. It is also possible to add some more sections, for example, checker of oral contraception.

Get pregnant and take care of your pregnancy
During the cycle Flo will show you the chance of getting pregnant. You can see an ovulation day on the screenshot. After getting pregnant the app will show you a baby in that circle, you will be able to check its growth and see what week you are on.

Make plans for future
It is very useful to have an approximate plan of your cycles. Sometimes it is very uncomfortable if your period starts surprisingly, so with Flo you can check when you have next period and build plans.

Learn new every day
Flo offers lots of articles on lots of themes. You can read almost everything - health, working out, beauty, diet and so on. Also it offers you everyday tips - if you mark your mood as sad, it will tell you how to help yourself to feel better.

I must say I really like this app and it is actually designed really pleasantly, it is easy to use. The only thing I really don‚Äôt like is almost every article is for premium accounts, and premium costs way too much. So without buying it you just get endless reminders to buy it.

Establishing a good balance between business life and private life is of great importance for employees to stay healthy both physically and psychologically. Continuous exposure to long working hours brings high levels of stress and it can lead to serious health problems; it might even lead people to suicide. 

In fact, countries‚Äô different working cultures and socio-economic factors can change the working hours that employers expect from their employees. 

Although the weekly working hours are officially 45 hours, 23% of the workers in Turkey have to work more than 60 hours per week. The rate of those who work more than 50 hours is 39 percent.



***
With long working hours, Turkey takes the first place among member countries of the Organization of Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) countries. The OECD data indicates that the weekly working time of the workers in Turkey is 50.7 hours.

The chart clarifies that Turkish people extremely work hard comparing to other OECD countries and beat others with a huge spread in term of working hours. This data is also driving the country down on other social rankings. But, at least, Turkey is working slightly shorter hours comparing to 2004 but it is still far from looking optimistically.

Approximately 6.5 million of the 30 million workers in Turkey are working at a minimum wage.¬†
***

Work life balance in Turkey: national holidays and working hours
